f the New York Game Awards 2018|url=https://www.axs.com/complete-list-of-winners-of-the-new-york-game-awards-2018-127527|website=[[AXS (company)|AXS]]|accessdate=January 28, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[21st Annual D.I.C.E. Awards]]\n| Racing Game of the Year\n| {{won}}\n| align=center|<ref>{{cite web|last=Makuch|first=Eddie|date=January 14, 2018|title=Game Of The Year Nominees Announced For DICE Awards|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/game-of-the-year-nominees-announced-for-dice-award/1100-6456107/|website=GameSpot|accessdate=January 17, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Makuch|first=Eddie|date=February 22, 2018|title=Legend Of Zelda: Breath Of The Wild Wins Game Of The Year At DICE Awards|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/legend-of-zelda-breath-of-the-wild-wins-game-of-th/1100-6456956/|website=GameSpot|accessdate=February 23, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Italian Video Game Awards\n| People's Choice\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://italianvideogameawards.com/awards|title=Italian Video Game Nominees and Winners 2018|website=Italian Video Game Awards|date=March 14, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180321193010/https://italianvideogameawards.com/awards|archivedate=March 21, 2018|url-status=dead|accessdate=June 3, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Family Game\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[2018 Kids' Choice Awards]]\n| Favorite Video Game\n| {{nom}}\n| align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nickpress.com/press-releases/2018/02/26/nickelodeon-announces-2018-kids-choice-awards-nominations|title=NICKELODEON ANNOUNCES 2018 KIDS\u2019 CHOICE AWARDS NOMINATIONS|website=[[Nick.com]]|publisher=[[Viacom (2005\u2013present)|Viacom]]|date=February 26, 2018|accessdate=March 3, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Drysdale|first=Jennifer|date=March 24, 2018|url=http://www.etonline.com/2018-kids-choice-awards-the-complete-winners-list-99000|title=2018 Kids' Choice Awards: The Complete Winners List|website=[[Entertainment Tonight]]|accessdate=March 25, 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==''Mario Kart 8 Deluxe''==\n{{Anchor|Mario Kart 8 Deluxe|Deluxe|Port|Nintendo Switch}}\nAn enhanced [[Nintendo Switch]] port titled {{nihongo foot|'''''Mario Kart 8 Deluxe'''''|\u30de\u30ea\u30aa\u30ab\u30fc\u30c88 \u30c7\u30e9\u30c3\u30af\u30b9|Mario K\u0101to Eito Derakkusu|lead=yes|group=lower-alpha}} was released worldwide on April 28, 2017.<ref name=\"The Verge\">{{cite news|last1=Gartenberg|first1=Chaim|title=Mario Kart 8 Deluxe is coming to the Nintendo Switch|url=https://www.theverge.com/2017/1/13/14243370/mario-kart-8-deluxe-announced-nintendo-switch-event|accessdate=January 13, 2017|work=The Verge|date=January 13, 2017}}</ref> This version includes all previously released DLC content, additional content, gameplay tweaks, [[1080p]] graphics at 60 [[frames per second]] while docked,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2017/03/mario_kart_8_deluxe_runs_at_60fps_in_1080p_when_docked|title=Mario Kart 8 Deluxe Runs at 60fps in 1080p When Docked|last=Forde|first=Matt|date=March 13, 2017|work=Nintendo Life|accessdate=August 17, 2017|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://venturebeat.com/2017/01/13/mario-kart-8-deluxe-on-nintendo-switch-runs-at-1080p-and-60-fps-on-tv-720p60-fps-in-handheld-mode/|title=Mario Kart 8 Deluxe on Nintendo Switch runs at 1080p and 60 FPS on TV; 720p/60 FPS in handheld mode|date=2017-01-14|website=VentureBeat|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-01}}</ref> and 720p at 60 frames per second in handheld mode.<ref name=\":0\" /> Some features in ''Deluxe'' are reworked or restored from previous generations of ''Mario Kart'' games: Battle Mode has eight new arenas and several gameplay modes; the Boo and Feather items are restored; and players can carry two items at once, even if they don't drag the first item. Six additional playable characters were added to the roster, including [[Bowser Jr.]], Dry Bones, [[King Boo]], Inkling Boys and Girls from ''[[Splatoon]]'', and an unlockable Gold Mario costume for [[Metal Mario]]. ''Deluxe'' includes new racing suits for [[Mii]] characters unlocked via [[Amiibo]], and additional kart parts for customization.<ref name=\"The Verge\" /> Nintendo's head of software development, Shinya Takahashi, confirmed in July 2018 that ''Mario Kart 8 Deluxe'' would receive further updates,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/mario-kart-8-deluxe-getting-more-updates-on-ninten/1100-6460414/|title=Mario Kart 8 Deluxe Getting More Updates On Nintendo Switch|first=Eddie|last=Makuch|date=July 20, 2018|publisher=}}</ref> with the first, a new vehicle and alternate costume for Link based on those seen in ''[[The Legend of Zelda: Breath of the Wild]]'', being released the same month.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/7/19/17593958/mario-kart-8-deluxe-update-link-zelda-breath-of-the-wild-nintendo-switch|title=Mario Kart 8 Deluxe update adds Link from Breath of the Wild|first=Michael|last=McWhertor|date=July 19, 2018|website=Polygon}}</ref> Updates have added support for [[Nintendo Labo]] peripherals as compatible controllers.<ref name=\"labo\" />\n\nThe port received critical acclaim with many critics highlighting the revamped battle mode as a welcome improvement over the Wii U version.<ref name=\"MetacriticSwitch\">{{cite web|title=Mario Kart 8 Deluxe for Switch reviews|url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/switch/mario-kart-8-deluxe|publisher=Metacritic|accessdate=April 28, 2017}}</ref> It holds a score of 92/100 on [[Metacritic]].<ref name=\"MetacriticSwitch\"/> IGN gave it a score of 9.3/10, stating that the game is \"just as amazing in 2017 as it was in 2014\".<ref name=\"IGNSwitch\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2017/04/20/mario-kart-8-deluxe-review|title=Mario Kart 8 Deluxe Review|last=Otero|first=Jose|date=April 20, 2017|website=IGN|access-date=July 4, 2017}}</ref> Eurogamer, referencing the revamped Battle Mode, stated that Nintendo fixed one of the game's only shortcomings in a \"generous port of a modern masterpiece\".<ref name=\"Eurogamer\">{{cite web|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2017-04-21-mario-kart-8-deluxe-review|title=Mario Kart 8 Deluxe review|last=Robinson|first=Martin|date=April 21, 2017|website=Eurogamer}}</ref>\n\n''Mario Kart 8 Deluxe'' was one of the best-selling games of 2017 at [[Amazon (company)|Amazon]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2017/4/28/15474658/mario-kart-8-deluxe-sales-amazon|title=Mario Kart 8 Deluxe is Amazon's best-selling game of 2017 so far|last=Sarkar|first=Samit|date=April 28, 2017|website=Polygon|access-date=August 17, 2017}}</ref> It became the first ''Mario'' game since ''[[Mario Kart Wii]]'' in 2008 and the first Nintendo game overall since [[Pok\u00e9mon Black and White|''Pok\u00e9mon Black'' and ''White Version'']] in 2011 to reach No. 1 on the charts in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Dayus|first1=Oscar|title=Top 10 UK Sales Chart: Mario Kart 8 Deluxe Is Nintendo's First No.1 For Six Years|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/top-10-uk-sales-chart-mario-kart-8-deluxe-is-ninte/1100-6449717/|website=GameSpot|accessdate=January 31, 2018}}</ref> ''Mario Kart 8 Deluxe'' became the fastest-selling game in the franchise's history, with more than 1.2 million copies sold worldwide within three days.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mashable.com/2017/05/01/mario-kart-8-deluxe-sales-record-breaking|title=Nintendo sold 1.2&nbsp;million copies of 'Mario Kart Deluxe' in three days|last=Rosenberg|first=Adam|publisher=Mashable|date=May 1, 2017}}</ref> By March 2018, more than nine million copies had been sold worldwide, ranking it among the [[List of best-selling Nintendo Switch video games|best-selling games on the platform]], only after ''[[Super Mario Odyssey]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Arif|first1=Shabana|title=Super Mario Odyssey Hits 10 Million Sales|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2018/04/26/super-mario-odyssey-hits-10-million-sales|website=IGN|accessdate=April 27, 2018}}</ref> Three months later, sales had surpassed ten million.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/en/finance/software/index.html|title=IR Information : Sales Data - Top Selling Title Sales Units|work=Nintendo Co., Ltd.|access-date=July 31, 2018|language=en}}</ref> {{As of |2019|12|31|df=US}}, total sales reached 22.96 million, and is currently the [[List of best-selling Nintendo Switch video games|best-selling Nintendo Switch game]].<ref>{{Cite web |url =https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/en/finance/software/index.html |title = IR Information : Sales Data - Top Selling Title Sales Units |date=December 31, 2019 |accessdate=January 30, 2019 |website=[[Nintendo]]}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|refs =\n\n<ref name=\"Hideki Konno, MK8, MTV interview\">{{cite web |url=http://multiplayerblog.mtv.com/2013/06/17/e3-2013-mario-kart-8-interview/ |title=E3 2013: Nintendo's Hideki Konno Pulls Back The Curtain On 'Mario Kart 8\u2032 |publisher=MTV |date=June 17, 2013 |accessdate=September 7, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130902100445/http://multiplayerblog.mtv.com/2013/06/17/e3-2013-mario-kart-8-interview |archivedate=September 2, 2013  }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"MK8 at Engadget\">{{cite web|last=Rigg |first=Jamie |url=https://www.engadget.com/2013/06/11/mario-kart-8/ |title=Mario Kart 8 launching on Wii U in spring 2014 (video) |work=Engadget |date=November 18, 2012 |accessdate=June 13, 2013}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"MK8 UK hardware\">{{cite web | title=Mario Kart 8 boosts UK Wii U hardware sales 666% | first=Tom | last=Ivan | date=June 2, 2014 | url=http://www.computerandvideogames.com/465552/mario-kart-8-boosts-uk-wii-u-hardware-sales-666/ | publisher=Computer and Video Games | accessdate=June 2, 2014 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Mario Kart 8 - More New Features Trailer\">{{YouTube | id=rLv0NH-lJUc | title=Wii U&nbsp;\u2013 Mario Kart 8&nbsp;\u2013 More New Features Trailer}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Mario Kart 8 Direct April 30, 2014\